Bad Design: 3

Description:
The pathway has separate entry and exit lanes, but people still have to cross each other near the gate. This makes the design less useful and causes confusion.

Source of Photograph:
(CAPTURED PICTURE)

Place:
VIT University, Vellore

Reasons why the design is bad:

Entry and exit paths meet near the gate.

People have to cross each other.

Causes confusion during busy times.

Does not improve pedestrian movement.


Suggested Improvement:

Make separate entry and exit paths until the gate.

Add clear direction signs.

Use barriers to guide people.

Widen the pathway near the gate.

Bad Design: Delete for Everyone Notification

Description:
Even after using "Delete for Everyone", the receiver still sees "This message was deleted.", creating unnecessary curiosity.

Source of Photograph: (Captured Picture)

Place:
WhatsApp Chat

Reasons why the design is bad:

Creates unnecessary curiosity.

Reduces user privacy.

Clutters the chat.

May cause misunderstandings.


Suggested Improvement:

Remove the message without any notification.

Add an option for silent deletion.

Keep the chat clean and private.
